<article id="main-col">
<h1 class="page-title">About Science</h1>
<p>
    <p class="dark">
<i><b>What is Science?</b></i><br>
       According to Merriam Webster's Dictionary, science is knowledge or a system of knowledge covering general truths or the operation of general laws especially as obtained and tested through scientific methods. 
       There are five main branches of science, which are: physical science, life science, earth science, social science, and formal science. On this website, I'm going to talk about the other branches of science that I find most fascinating.
          </p>
                    
<i><b>What are the main branches of Science?</b></i><br>
The three main branches of science are physical science, life science, and earth science.<br><br>

<b>Physical Science</b><br><ul>

<li>The Study of how non-living things interact
</li>
<li>Includes chemistry, physics, and astronomy
</li>
<li>Focuses on the laws that govern inanimate objects</li><br></ul>

<b>Life science</b><br>
<ul>
<li>The study of how living things grow, develop, and reproduce</li>

<li>Includes biology, botany, and zoology</li>

<li>Also includes genetics, nutrition, and medicine</li><br></ul>

<b>Earth science</b>
<ul>

<li>The study of the history and structure of Earth</li>

<li>Includes geology, paleontology, meteorology, and oceanography</li>

<li>Focuses on the physical components that make up Earth</li><br></ul>

<b>Other branches of science:</b><br>

<b>Social science</b>: Focuses on human life and its relationship with the environment<br>

<b>Formal science</b>: Studies formal language disciplines such as statistics, mathematics, and logic
</p>
</article>

